snippet: An attack in Baquba left 20 people dead and heightened concerns about violence in advance of local elections scheduled for April 20.
abstract: Two bombs explode and rip through tent at political rally in Baquba, Iraq, where voters and candidates had gathered for lunch, leaving 20 people dead and nearly 55 wounded; attack heightens concerns about violence before local elections scheduled for April 20.

byline.contributor: An employee of The New York Times contributed reporting from Diyala Province, Iraq.

lead_paragraph: An attack in Baquba left 20 people dead and heightened concerns about violence in advance of local elections scheduled for April 20.

headline.main: 2 Weeks Before Iraqi Local Elections, Deadly Bombs Hit Campaign Event
headline.print_headline: 2 Weeks Before Iraqi Local Elections, Deadly Bombs Hit Campaign Event
